contentrichtext.text: '''Horsey''' may refer to: * [[Horse]], in baby-talk ==Places== The name comes from Anglo-Saxon "hors-eg" and means horse-island. * [[Horsey, Norfolk]] * [[Horsey, Somerset]] * [[Horsey Down]], near [[Lechlade]] * [[Horsey Island]], near Walton-on-the-Naze in Essex * [[Horsey Island, Devon]], a nature reserve near [[Braunton]] * [[Horsea Islands]], two islands in [[Portsmouth]] harbour * [[Horsey Mere]], one of the Norfolk Broads in the east of England * [[Horse Eye]], on the Pevensey Levels near [[Eastbourne]] ==People== * [[David Horsey]], editorial cartoonist * [[David Horsey (golfer)]], professional golfer * [[Edward Horsey]], conspirator against Queen Mary * [[John Horsey (died 1546)]] (1489-1546), knight of Henry VIII * [[John Horsey (died 1564)]] (1510-1564/65), knight of Henry VIII, son of above * [[Michael Horsey]], Philadelphia politician * [[Outerbridge Horsey (senator)]] (1777-1842), lawyer and U.S. Senator from Delaware == Music == * [[Horsey (album)]], album by [[Current 93]] {{disambig}}
